  "prompt": "Where can I find startup advisors?",
  "response": "Here are several ways to find startup advisors:\n\n1. Online Platforms\n- LinkedIn\n- AngelList\n- FounderNation\n- MentorCruise\n- SCORE\n\n2. Networking Events\n- Startup conferences\n- Tech meetups\n- Industry-specific networking events\n- Entrepreneurship workshops\n\n3. Accelerator and Incubator Programs\n- Y Combinator\n- Techstars\n- 500 Startups\n- Local startup accelerators\n\n4. Professional Organizations\n- Chamber of Commerce\n- Industry-specific associations\n- Entrepreneurship groups\n\n5. University Resources\n- Alumni networks\n- Entrepreneurship centers\n- Startup programs\n\n6. Online Communities\n- Reddit startup communities\n- Startup forums\n- Facebook/LinkedIn groups\n\n7. Personal Connections\n- Former colleagues\n- Professional contacts\n- Industry experts\n- Investors\n\n8. Advisor Matching Services\n- AdvisoryCloud\n- GLG (Gerson Lehrman Group)\n- Expert360\n\n9. Local Startup Ecosystems\n- Coworking spaces\n- Innovation hubs\n- Local startup communities\n\nTips:\n- Be clear about your needs\n- Look for relevant industry experience\n- Offer equity or compensation\n- Build genuine relationships",
